==noun==
# [[item]]s placed on a [[stage]] to create a [[scene]] or scenario in which [[actor]]s perform a [[play]] in a [[theatre]] or [[motion picture]].Usually the term "props" is reserved for [[object]]s with which an actor interacts (e.g. a [[glass]], a [[book]] or a [[weapon]]). Larger items adding to the scene, (e.g. [[chair]]s) are considered part of the [[set]]. The plural '''props'''.
# Props is also congratulatory praise given to a person.

===Related terms===
warm props - [[extra]]s or people with non-speaking roles usually used to make a scene look more realistic.